        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Mesopotamian pottery styles [300107735], Mesopotamian (culture or style) [300019828], Near Eastern (Early Western World) [300019571], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the pottery style found in northern Mesopotamia during the Mitannian period from about 1500 to 1300 BCE. The style is characterized by painted vessels decorated with white designs on a dark ground, of which goblets are the most common form.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica encontrado en Mesopotamia del norte durante el período de Mitaní de aproximadamente 1500 al 1300 a.C. El estilo se caracteriza por vasos pintados decorados con diseños blancos en una base oscura en que las copas son la forma más común.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van het aardewerk uit de Mittanische periode in Mesopotamië van circa 1500 tot 1300 v. Chr. De stijl kenmerkt zich door de geschilderde vazen, met witte dessins op een donkere achtergrond, waarvan de bekervorm het meest werd gebruikt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指約自西元前1500年至西元前1300年間的邁坦尼時代，於美索不達米亞北部發展的陶器風格。此風格的特色是在黑底陶身繪上白色設計作為裝飾的彩繪陶器，高腳杯為最常見的形制。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
